Additional material:
R. A. Johnson collected specimens from two colonies of T. pomonae in Sonora , Mexico ( 5 km east San Pedro de la Cueva ;
27-IV-2004
). The nests had been found in the shade in a mesic canyon and had no nest mound. Deciduous thorn scrub produced an abundant leaf litter layer on the bottom of the canyon.
